Digiturk Gets 500 Million Liras Tax Bill, Sabah Says

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-05-31T06:04:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/turkey-s-karamehmet-gets-new-500-million-tax-bill-sabah-says.html
(Corrects currency throughout.)  Cukurova Holding owner Mehmet Emin Karamehmet received an additional 500 million liras tax fine for
his cable broadcasting company Digiturk, bringing his total tax
debt in  Turkey  to 2.2 billion liras, Sabah newspaper reported.  The new bill is for the period 2005 to 2009 and includes
170 million liras in unpaid taxes, 170 million liras in
penalties and 160 million liras in interest, the Istanbul-based
newspaper reported. The fines were imposed after an
investigation by the  finance ministry , it said.  Tax authorities earlier this month seized 1.7 billion liras
worth of Karamehmetâ€™s shares in mobile phone operator Turkcell
Iletisim Hizmetleri AS, of which he was formerly chairman.  To contact the reporter on this story:
